  <section xml:id="cockpit-managing-virtual-networks-creating">
    <title>Creating a virtual network</title>
    <para>
      To create a virtual network, proceed as follows:
    </para>
    <procedure>
      <step>
        <para>
          Click the <guimenu>Virtual machines</guimenu> plugin.
        </para>
      </step>
      <step>
        <para>
          Click  <guilabel>Networks</guilabel>.
        </para>
      </step>
      <step>
        <para>
          Click <guimenu>Create virtual network</guimenu> and enter the following information:
        </para>
        <variablelist>
          <varlistentry>
            <term><guilabel>Name</guilabel></term>
          <listitem>
            <para>
              provide a name for the virtual network
            </para>
          </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
          <varlistentry>
            <term><guilabel>Forward mode</guilabel></term>
          <listitem>
            <para>
              Select any of the following modes:
            </para>
            <itemizedlist>
              <listitem>
                <para>
                  <guilabel>NAT</guilabel> - guest machine can perform outgoing connections without
                  restrictions. Incoming connections is from other guest on the same network or the
                  host, other incoming connections are blocked by <literal>iptables</literal> rules.
                </para>
              </listitem>
              <listitem>
                <para>
                  <guilabel>open</guilabel>
                </para>
              </listitem>
              <listitem>
                <para>
                  <guilabel>none</guilabel> - guest cannot access the Internet. Connections are
                  possible only within the virtual network.
                </para>
              </listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
          </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
          <varlistentry>
            <term><guilabel>Device</guilabel></term>
            <listitem>
              <para>
                Applies for the <literal>NAT</literal> forward mode. Select the physical networking device.
              </para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
          <varlistentry>
            <term><guilabel>IP configuration</guilabel></term>
            <listitem>
              <para>
                select which IP protocol version should be used and enter the following information:
              </para>
              <itemizedlist>
                <listitem>
                  <para>
                    <guilabel>IPv4 address</guilabel> or <guilabel>IPv6 address</guilabel> - assign
                    an IP address to the network.
                  </para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                  <para>
                    <guilabel>Mask or prefix length</guilabel> - for the IPv4 address. Enter either
                    the prefix length&mdash;default and common value is 24, or enter the subnet
                    mask, for example, 255.255.255.0&mdash;corresponding to the 24bits prefix
                    length. The prefix length determines how many bits of the IP address denotes
                    the network part of the IP address.
                  </para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                  <para>
                    <guilabel>Prefix length</guilabel> - for the IPv6 address. A common value is 64.
                  </para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                  <para>
                    <guilabel>Set DHCP range</guilabel> - if checked, enter the start and end of
                    the IP addresses range that will be assigned to quest within the network.
                  </para>
                </listitem>
              </itemizedlist>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
        </variablelist>
      </step>
    </procedure>
